00:02:59.568 --> 00:03:03.318
First, what is clear
and accessible writing?

00:03:03.897 --> 00:03:08.051
We can define accessible writing
as one which is open

00:03:08.051 --> 00:03:12.791
and usable by every person regardless
of their characteristics

00:03:12.791 --> 00:03:15.957
and the technologies they use to read.

00:03:16.839 --> 00:03:19.339
Who needs accessible writing?

00:03:19.814 --> 00:03:24.160
Well, usually, the first people to come
to mind are people

00:03:24.160 --> 00:03:28.482
with a visual impairment,
those with cognitive disabilities,

00:03:28.482 --> 00:03:29.957
people with dyslexia

00:03:29.957 --> 00:03:33.957
or with specific
neurodevelopmental conditions.

00:03:34.716 --> 00:03:38.959
We must also consider so many
other people with physical, cognitive,

00:03:38.959 --> 00:03:41.189
and social conditions who can benefit

00:03:41.189 --> 00:03:44.856
from these accessibility
writing techniques

00:03:45.936 --> 00:03:49.919
such as people with a low level
of schooling, older individuals,

00:03:49.919 --> 00:03:54.996
people who do not speak English
or your language as a first language,

00:03:54.996 --> 00:03:59.428
people who have problems with anxiety,
stress, fatigue,

00:03:59.428 --> 00:04:03.048
people who are in a hurry
and have little time to read

00:04:03.048 --> 00:04:05.908
and assimilate the information
they're looking for

00:04:05.908 --> 00:04:09.693
Basically, there's a very broad range
of people that can benefit

00:04:09.693 --> 00:04:14.276
from the accessibility techniques
we'll discuss today.

00:04:17.347 --> 00:04:20.514
